Author: susarla#5544
Content:
Hi
In the first lecture ... David sir.. mentions that each core can do task and 4 cores means 4 task parallely at a time.
Does that mean a processor is 2ghz .. so each core can do 2billion task at a time or those 2 billion tasks are divided to 4 cores ?

Author: _ğ•„ğ•£. ğ•Šğ•™ğ•–ğ•–ğ•¡#4604
Content: @susarla in the case of a CPU processor, each core will have an individual clock speed (essentially how many tasks per time). That means a 2ghz 4 core processor is running 4 cores, each at 2ghz. But nowadays, CPUs may have different speeds for different cores so as to be more efficient in certain tasks.

Author: susarla#5544
Content:
@_ğ•„ğ•£. ğ•Šğ•™ğ•–ğ•–ğ•¡ so assuming that each core clock speeds are same ... So it's like 2billion things (say instructions) * 4cores per second . 
Thank you :)
